399 static const int kInternalFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
400 static const int kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback = 2;
401 
402 template <typename T>
403 class WeakCallbackInfo {
404  public:
405  typedef void (*Callback)(const WeakCallbackInfo<T>& data);
406 
407  WeakCallbackInfo(Isolate* isolate, T* parameter,
408  void* embedder_fields[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback],
409  Callback* callback)
410  : isolate_(isolate), parameter_(parameter), callback_(callback) {
411  for (int i = 0; i < kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback; ++i) {
412  embedder_fields_[i] = embedder_fields[i];
413  }
414  }
415 
416  V8_INLINE Isolate* GetIsolate() const { return isolate_; }
417  V8_INLINE T* GetParameter() const { return parameter_; }
418  V8_INLINE void* GetInternalField(int index) const;
419 
420  // When first called, the embedder MUST Reset() the Global which triggered the
421  // callback. The Global itself is unusable for anything else. No v8 other api
422  // calls may be called in the first callback. Should additional work be
423  // required, the embedder must set a second pass callback, which will be
424  // called after all the initial callbacks are processed.
425  // Calling SetSecondPassCallback on the second pass will immediately crash.
426  void SetSecondPassCallback(Callback callback) const { *callback_ = callback; }
427 
428  private:
429  Isolate* isolate_;
430  T* parameter_;
431  Callback* callback_;
432  void* embedder_fields_[kEmbedderFieldsInWeakCallback];
433 };
434 
435 
436 // kParameter will pass a void* parameter back to the callback, kInternalFields
437 // will pass the first two internal fields back to the callback, kFinalizer
438 // will pass a void* parameter back, but is invoked before the object is
439 // actually collected, so it can be resurrected. In the last case, it is not
440 // possible to request a second pass callback.
441 enum class WeakCallbackType { kParameter, kInternalFields, kFinalizer };

632 template <class T, class M> class Persistent : public PersistentBase<T> {
633  public:
637  V8_INLINE Persistent() : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {}
643  template <class S>
644  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, Local<S> that)
645  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
646  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
647  }
653  template <class S, class M2>
654  V8_INLINE Persistent(Isolate* isolate, const Persistent<S, M2>& that)
655  : PersistentBase<T>(PersistentBase<T>::New(isolate, *that)) {
656  TYPE_CHECK(T, S);
657  }
664  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent& that) : PersistentBase<T>(nullptr) {
665  Copy(that);
666  }
667  template <class S, class M2>
668  V8_INLINE Persistent(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) : PersistentBase<T>(0) {
669  Copy(that);
670  }
671  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent& that) {
672  Copy(that);
673  return *this;
674  }
675  template <class S, class M2>
676  V8_INLINE Persistent& operator=(const Persistent<S, M2>& that) { // NOLINT
677  Copy(that);
678  return *this;
679  }
685  V8_INLINE ~Persistent() {
686  if (M::kResetInDestructor) this->Reset();
687  }
688 
689  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
690  template <class S>
691  V8_INLINE static Persistent<T>& Cast(const Persistent<S>& that) { // NOLINT
692 #ifdef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
693  // If we're going to perform the type check then we have to check
694  // that the handle isn't empty before doing the checked cast.
695  if (!that.IsEmpty()) T::Cast(*that);
696 #endif
697  return reinterpret_cast<Persistent<T>&>(const_cast<Persistent<S>&>(that));
698  }
699 
700  // TODO(dcarney): this is pretty useless, fix or remove
701  template <class S>
702  V8_INLINE Persistent<S>& As() const { // NOLINT
703  return Persistent<S>::Cast(*this);
704  }
705 
706  private:
707  friend class Isolate;
708  friend class Utils;
709  template<class F> friend class Local;
710  template<class F1, class F2> friend class Persistent;
711  template<class F> friend class ReturnValue;
712 
713  explicit V8_INLINE Persistent(T* that) : PersistentBase<T>(that) {}
714  V8_INLINE T* operator*() const { return this->val_; }
715  template<class S, class M2>
716  V8_INLINE void Copy(const Persistent<S, M2>& that);
717 };

1410  rejected(false),

1412 
1413  // If buffer_policy is BufferNotOwned, the caller keeps the ownership of
1414  // data and guarantees that it stays alive until the CachedData object is
1415  // destroyed. If the policy is BufferOwned, the given data will be deleted
1416  // (with delete[]) when the CachedData object is destroyed.

1418  BufferPolicy buffer_policy = BufferNotOwned);
1419  ~CachedData();

1421  // which will be called when V8 no longer needs the data.
1422  const uint8_t* data;
1423  int length;
1424  bool rejected;
1425  BufferPolicy buffer_policy;
1426 
1427  // Prevent copying.
1428  CachedData(const CachedData&) = delete;

1430  };

7047 struct JitCodeEvent {
7048  enum EventType {
7049  CODE_ADDED,
7050  CODE_MOVED,
7051  CODE_REMOVED,
7052  CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO,
7053  CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING,
7054  CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING
7055  };
7056  // Definition of the code position type. The "POSITION" type means the place
7057  // in the source code which are of interest when making stack traces to
7058  // pin-point the source location of a stack frame as close as possible.
7059  // The "STATEMENT_POSITION" means the place at the beginning of each
7060  // statement, and is used to indicate possible break locations.
7061  enum PositionType { POSITION, STATEMENT_POSITION };
7062 
7063  // There are two different kinds of JitCodeEvents, one for JIT code generated
7064  // by the optimizing compiler, and one for byte code generated for the
7065  // interpreter. For JIT_CODE events, the |code_start| member of the event
7066  // points to the beginning of jitted assembly code, while for BYTE_CODE
7067  // events, |code_start| points to the first bytecode of the interpreted
7068  // function.
7069  enum CodeType { BYTE_CODE, JIT_CODE };
7070 
7071  // Type of event.
7072  EventType type;
7073  CodeType code_type;
7074  // Start of the instructions.
7075  void* code_start;
7076  // Size of the instructions.
7077  size_t code_len;
7078  // Script info for CODE_ADDED event.
7079  Local<UnboundScript> script;
7080  // User-defined data for *_LINE_INFO_* event. It's used to hold the source
7081  // code line information which is returned from the
7082  // CODE_START_LINE_INFO_RECORDING event. And it's passed to subsequent
7083  // CODE_ADD_LINE_POS_INFO and CODE_END_LINE_INFO_RECORDING events.
7084  void* user_data;
7085 
7086  struct name_t {
7087  // Name of the object associated with the code, note that the string is not
7088  // zero-terminated.
7089  const char* str;
7090  // Number of chars in str.
7091  size_t len;
7092  };
7093 
7094  struct line_info_t {
7095  // PC offset
7096  size_t offset;
7097  // Code position
7098  size_t pos;
7099  // The position type.
7100  PositionType position_type;

7122 enum RAILMode : unsigned {
7123  // Response performance mode: In this mode very low virtual machine latency
7124  // is provided. V8 will try to avoid JavaScript execution interruptions.
7125  // Throughput may be throttled.
7126  PERFORMANCE_RESPONSE,
7127  // Animation performance mode: In this mode low virtual machine latency is
7128  // provided. V8 will try to avoid as many JavaScript execution interruptions
7129  // as possible. Throughput may be throttled. This is the default mode.
7130  PERFORMANCE_ANIMATION,
7131  // Idle performance mode: The embedder is idle. V8 can complete deferred work
7132  // in this mode.
7133  PERFORMANCE_IDLE,
7134  // Load performance mode: In this mode high throughput is provided. V8 may
7135  // turn off latency optimizations.
7136  PERFORMANCE_LOAD
7137 };

9012 template <class T>
9013 class Maybe {
9014  public:
9015  V8_INLINE bool IsNothing() const { return !has_value_; }
9016  V8_INLINE bool IsJust() const { return has_value_; }
9017 
9021  V8_INLINE T ToChecked() const { return FromJust(); }
9022 
9027  V8_INLINE void Check() const {
9028  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9029  }
9030 
9035  V8_WARN_UNUSED_RESULT V8_INLINE bool To(T* out) const {
9036  if (V8_LIKELY(IsJust())) *out = value_;
9037  return IsJust();
9038  }
9039 
9044  V8_INLINE T FromJust() const {
9045  if (V8_UNLIKELY(!IsJust())) V8::FromJustIsNothing();
9046  return value_;
9047  }
9048 
9053  V8_INLINE T FromMaybe(const T& default_value) const {
9054  return has_value_ ? value_ : default_value;
9055  }
9056 
9057  V8_INLINE bool operator==(const Maybe& other) const {
9058  return (IsJust() == other.IsJust()) &&
9059  (!IsJust() || FromJust() == other.FromJust());
9060  }
9061 
9062  V8_INLINE bool operator!=(const Maybe& other) const {
9063  return !operator==(other);
9064  }
9065 
9066  private:
9067  Maybe() : has_value_(false) {}
9068  explicit Maybe(const T& t) : has_value_(true), value_(t) {}
9069 
9070  bool has_value_;
9071  T value_;

9077 };

10313 Local<Value> Object::GetInternalField(int index) {
10314 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10315  typedef internal::Address A;
10316  typedef internal::Internals I;
10317  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
10318  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10319  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10320  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10321  if (instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10322  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10323  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType) {
10324  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10325  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(obj, offset);
10326 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
10327  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
10328  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
10329  value = I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(obj, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
10330 #endif
10331  internal::Isolate* isolate =
10332  internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(obj);
10333  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
10334  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10335  }
10336 #endif
10337  return SlowGetInternalField(index);
10338 }
10339 
10340 
10341 void* Object::GetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(int index) {
10342 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10343  typedef internal::Address A;
10344  typedef internal::Internals I;
10345  A obj = *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this);
10346  // Fast path: If the object is a plain JSObject, which is the common case, we
10347  // know where to find the internal fields and can return the value directly.
10348  auto instance_type = I::GetInstanceType(obj);
10349  if (V8_LIKELY(instance_type == I::kJSObjectType ||
10350  instance_type == I::kJSApiObjectType ||
10351  instance_type == I::kJSSpecialApiObjectType)) {
10352  int offset = I::kJSObjectHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10353  return I::ReadRawField<void*>(obj, offset);
10354  }
10355 #endif
10356  return SlowGetAlignedPointerFromInternalField(index);
10357 }

10919 int64_t Isolate::AdjustAmountOfExternalAllocatedMemory(
10920  int64_t change_in_bytes) {
10921  typedef internal::Internals I;
10922  constexpr int64_t kMemoryReducerActivationLimit = 32 * 1024 * 1024;
10923  int64_t* external_memory = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10924  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryOffset);
10925  int64_t* external_memory_limit = reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(
10926  reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) + I::kExternalMemoryLimitOffset);
10927  int64_t* external_memory_at_last_mc =
10928  reinterpret_cast<int64_t*>(reinterpret_cast<uint8_t*>(this) +
10929  I::kExternalMemoryAtLastMarkCompactOffset);
10930 
10931  // Embedders are weird: we see both over- and underflows here. Perform the
10932  // addition with unsigned types to avoid undefined behavior.
10933  const int64_t amount =
10934  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(change_in_bytes) +
10935  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory));
10936  *external_memory = amount;
10937 
10938  int64_t allocation_diff_since_last_mc =
10939  static_cast<int64_t>(static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory) -
10940  static_cast<uint64_t>(*external_memory_at_last_mc));
10941  // Only check memory pressure and potentially trigger GC if the amount of
10942  // external memory increased.
10943  if (allocation_diff_since_last_mc > kMemoryReducerActivationLimit) {
10944  CheckMemoryPressure();
10945  }
10946 
10947  if (change_in_bytes < 0) {
10948  const int64_t lower_limit = *external_memory_limit + change_in_bytes;
10949  if (lower_limit > I::kExternalAllocationSoftLimit)
10950  *external_memory_limit = lower_limit;
10951  } else if (change_in_bytes > 0 && amount > *external_memory_limit) {
10952  ReportExternalAllocationLimitReached();
10953  }
10954  return *external_memory;
10955 }

10957 Local<Value> Context::GetEmbedderData(int index) {
10958 #ifndef V8_ENABLE_CHECKS
10959  typedef internal::Address A;
10960  typedef internal::Internals I;
10961  A ctx = *reinterpret_cast<const A*>(this);
10962  A embedder_data =
10963  I::ReadTaggedPointerField(ctx, I::kNativeContextEmbedderDataOffset);
10964  int value_offset =
10965  I::kEmbedderDataArrayHeaderSize + (I::kEmbedderDataSlotSize * index);
10966  A value = I::ReadRawField<A>(embedder_data, value_offset);
10967 #ifdef V8_COMPRESS_POINTERS
10968  // We read the full pointer value and then decompress it in order to avoid
10969  // dealing with potential endiannes issues.
10970  value =
10971  I::DecompressTaggedAnyField(embedder_data, static_cast<int32_t>(value));
10972 #endif
10973  internal::Isolate* isolate = internal::IsolateFromNeverReadOnlySpaceObject(
10974  *reinterpret_cast<A*>(this));
10975  A* result = HandleScope::CreateHandle(isolate, value);
10976  return Local<Value>(reinterpret_cast<Value*>(result));
10977 #else
10978  return SlowGetEmbedderData(index);
10979 #endif
10980 }
